1 'use strict';
  2 
  3 var _ = require('underscore');
  4 
  5 module.exports = function(AV) {
  6 
  7   /**
  8    * Constructs a new AV.Error object with the given code and message.
  9    * @param {Number} code An error code constant from <code>AV.Error</code>.
 10    * @param {String} message A detailed description of the error.
 11    * @class
 12    *
 13    * <p>Class used for all objects passed to error callbacks.</p>
 14    */
 15   AV.Error = function(code, message) {
 16     this.code = code;
 17     this.message = message;
 18   };
 19 
 20   _.extend(AV.Error, /** @lends AV.Error */ {

 31      * @constant
 32      */
 33     INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR: 1,
 34 
 35     /**
 36      * Error code indicating the connection to the AV servers failed.
 37      * @constant
 38      */
 39     CONNECTION_FAILED: 100,
 40 
 41     /**

 44      */
 45     OBJECT_NOT_FOUND: 101,

 54     /**
